<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="relief-n">relief <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /rɪ'liːf/    美 /rɪ'liːf/  </p>
<p>[U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(痛苦等的) 减轻；宽慰：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>To our</strong> great <strong>relief</strong>, the accident caused little damage.
令我们十分宽慰的是，事故造成的损失很小。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The doctor said it was only a slight wound. <strong>What a relief</strong>! 
医生说只是轻伤。谢天谢地！</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Those who suffer from headache will find they get relief from this medicine.  
那些饱受头痛折磨的人将会发现使用这种药可以缓解疼痛。</p><footer>2010 山东</footer></div>

<h4 id="2-aid">2.★ <strong>救济物 (aid)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>send relief to flood victims 
将救济物资运送给遭受洪灾的灾民</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="in-with-relief">in / with relief</h3>
<p>1.<strong>如释重负；松了口气：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Hearing that he had passed the exam, he sighed in / with relief.
听说自己通过了考试，他松了口气。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— Don’t worry, Mum. The doctor said it was only the flu.
— What relief! I’ll tell Dad there’s nothing serious.  （2012 江苏改 改错）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. relief 前加 a  </p></div>